---
import TerminalPage from '../layouts/TerminalPage.astro';
---

<TerminalPage
  title="about"
  command="beixu@home:~$ cat /about"
  description="AI architect and product builder across cloud infrastructure, agents, embodied intelligence, and clinical AI."
>
  <section class="terminal-output">
    <p class="section-title">Profile</p>
    <p>
      beixu is an AI architect and product builder turning research-grade
      intelligence into deployable systems. His work spans cloud-native AI
      infrastructure, agentic workflows, quadruped robotics, and clinical AI
      systems for cardiopulmonary assessment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="terminal-output grid-two">
    <article>
      <p class="file-command">infra.txt</p>
      <p>
        Built cloud, container, resource scheduling, GPU management, big data,
        private cloud, microservices, and multi-cloud platform architecture at
        HP, TalkingData, and Tencent Cloud.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <p class="file-command">agents.txt</p>
      <p>
        Designs evidence-grounded agents, mono-agent runtimes, clinical agents,
        tool execution loops, and human-in-the-loop workflows where outputs stay
        inspectable.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <p class="file-command">robotics.txt</p>
      <p>
        Led product and R&D direction for quadruped robot systems, including
        inspection scenarios, perception, motion control, task execution, and
        prototype validation.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <p class="file-command">clinical-ai.txt</p>
      <p>
        Builds CPET-related AI models, datasets, review workbenches, and
        decision-support systems for physiological signals, risk identification,
        and cardiopulmonary function assessment.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="terminal-output grid-two">
    <article>
      <p class="file-command">education.txt</p>
      <p>
        Master's degree in Artificial Intelligence from the University of Surrey;
        bachelor's degree in Computer Science from Peking University.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <p class="file-command">current-mode.txt</p>
      <p>
        Exploring the next startup chapter with builders, researchers, and teams
        working on serious AI infrastructure and applied intelligence.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</TerminalPage>
